# Instance segmentation with neural networks based on aerial images
This project is about generating building footprints from orthophotos (i.e. aerial imagery) using deep learning.


## Installation
If the server should be run on a windows machine, make sure the Visual C++ Build Tools are installed.

Otherwise the installation of the python requirements will fail (pycocotools needs to be built).

`pip install git+https://github.com/philferriere/cocoapi.git#egg=pycocotools^&subdirectory=PythonAPI`


## Training Data
I've written a script that generates training data (i.e. ortophoto + binary masks) from Microsoft Bing in combination with Open Street Map (OSM).
Starting from a bounding box, the corresponding image data is downloaded from Bing and binary masks are being generated based on the vector data from OSM.

The script can be found at ```core/downloader.py```. In order for the script to be able to access the Bing REST imagery service,
a file ```secrets.py``` has to be existing in the root folder of the project and its content should be like this:

```python
BING_KEY = "your bing key comes here"
```

### Usage
To download all defined bboxes run:

```python -m core.downloader```

To download only a specific bbox run:

```python -m core.downloader {bbox_name}```
